12 12-8-703. Missing Endangered Adult Advisory System.
13 (a) There is established a standardized system to aid in the search of
14 missing adults to be known as the Missing Endangered Adult Advisory System.
15 (b) The Division of the Arkansas State Police shall serve as the
16 coordinating law enforcement agency to disseminate appropriate advisories
17 under the Missing Endangered Adult Advisory System.
18 (c)(1) The Missing Endangered Adult Advisory System shall be used for
19 a missing adult who does not meet the criteria for activation of the Arkansas
20 Silver Alert System who has:
21 (A) A mental or cognitive disability that is not
22 Alzheimerâ€™s disease or a dementia-related disorder;
23 (B) An intellectual disability, developmental disability,
24 or brain injury; or
25 (C) Another physical, mental, or emotional disability that
26 is not related to substance abuse.
27 (2) The Missing Endangered Adult Advisory Stytem will not be
28 activated for a person who is determined to be suicidal.
29 (d) The Missing Endangered Adult Advisory System shall have safeguards
30 in place to ensure that activation of the Missing Endangered Adult Advisory
31 System:
32 (1) Is the only viable means by which the missing adult is
33 likely to be returned to safety;
34 (2) Provides for the protection of the privacy, dignity, and
35 independence of the missing adult;
36 (3) Prevents the inadvertent or unnecessary broadcasting or
